## upstream

OpenClaw PR #67921 — "make channel startup non-blocking to improve gateway readiness"

## what it does

Changes channel startup from a blocking synchronous process to a fully async one using `Promise.allSettled()` instead of sequential error handling:

1. All channel modules initialize concurrently
2. Failures in one channel do not block others
3. Gateway HTTP server becomes ready before all channels finish loading
4. A summary of failed modules is logged but does not throw
5. Users can access the gateway UI immediately while broken channels are repaired

## why it fits nessie

Nessie's Mattermost connection is the primary channel. If the Mattermost plugin has a configuration issue (missing credentials, network timeout), it should not prevent the entire Nessie gateway from starting. Other agents and internal functions should remain available even if the external Mattermost integration is temporarily down.

This pattern also enables:
- Partial availability during version upgrades (some channels up, some not)
- Faster startup when multiple channels are configured
- Better debuggability (all channel errors surfaced at once, not one-at-a-time)

## suggested implementation

```typescript
// In server startup (server-startup-post-attach.ts):
// Before: await startChannels();
// After:
void (async () => {
  const results = await Promise.allSettled(
    channelConfigs.map(ch => startChannel(ch))
  );
  const failures = results
    .filter(r => r.status === 'rejected')
    .map((r, i) => ({ channel: channelConfigs[i].name, reason: r.reason }));
  if (failures.length > 0) {
    log.warn('Some channels failed to start', { failures });
  }
})();
```

